FBIS3-55263 "drsov005_d_94006" FBIS-SOV-94-005 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Jan 1994 Regional Affairs Groznyy Accuses Russia of Reluctance To Quit Gendarme Role LD0601172494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1427 GMT 6 Jan 94 LD0601172494 Moscow INTERFAX Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The Chechen Republic has described the proposal by the Central Election Commission that it take part in the parliamentary elections on March 13 as an ultimatum which will aggravate confrontation. INTERFAX correspondents report that the official Groznyy accused Russia of unwillingness to quit the gendarme approach, as well as the policy of threats and intimidation. The Chechen Republic believes that the date of March 13 is nothing else than a new deadline for the existence of the Chechen Republic to be possibly followed by punishment of the "obstinate".
